caption: We are in love with this stores. We been drinking these teas and stop drinking sodas. Really good and relaxing

This place became our favourite Poke place in the neighbourhood.  Their Poke Bowls are amazing delicious. They have a variety of options including Tofu and Vegeterian Chicken. It's nice to have an alternative to Tofu to stay on a vegetarian meal.  Their bubble teas are delicious too and goes well with a Poke. 😉  They are a great place to go for Poke.
Made my own poke bowl, everything was super fresh, tasted delicious!!
Great food the sushi was great the 🌮 taxcos even better great location great service ✅⭐⭐⭐⭐
The bowls are really big, and very tasty
Fresh great tasting poke bowls and they offer more than poke. They have some great noodles soups and good bubble tea drinks. Plenty of options to create your own or just order their signature dishes.
Got a Rose Milk Tea and Lychee Mojito. Both were refreshing and delicious.
Best Poke bowls EVER!

I've been to this several times and the guy with glasses isnt very friendly. The portion he gave was super small. He never smiles and speaks I'll of other customers. Quite unprofessional in my opinion. I like the chain at bensonhurst, Brooklyn better.
Ramen was very bland, tasted like water
Tasted terrible. Don't get the zucchini noodles, they're gross.
Not nearly enough poke to call it a poke bowl. Light on toppings. Just really isn’t worth the amount you pay. Mars Tea is good though; the only thing I’d recommend.

Food was just ok. Not good enough to overlook the unfriendly attitude from the two servers. The portions are very small for the price. As a previous comment mentioned, you can literally count 8 tiny pieces of tuna. I tried to get several toppings to replace the fish they didn't give but they were stingy with those too.  I won't be back

My go to spot in the area for affordable poke bowl. Plenty of options to choose from but one of my favorite proteins there is the baby octopus as that is not typically offered at other poke places. Unlimited toppings are a plus. A variety of bubble tea drinks and egg waffle desserts are offered as well if you have a sweet tooth and want to round out your meal with dessert. The space is a bit cozy but open layout. There's even a backyard with some seating when the weather is warmer.

Came to the place at 9 the food tasted amazing. Fresh and nice. The place is nice and has a goodlook to it. The food selection is what you would expect at your everyday poké restaurant but for some reason this is the best experience I’ve had in recent years with poké. Good place and would highly recommend. The staff is awesome as well.
LOVE THIS POKE SPOT
Yes this is the place to eat, love it, will visit often
Literally counted 8 cubes of tuna that they gave me. 10$ embarrassing. The veg was tasty so that’s why they got 3 stars
Great variety in menu, and fresh juice option great as well.

Would like to talk to the manager about my situation that happened to me here, never again will I support this place also will encourage my fellow coworkers to avoid this place also.  Will file complaint with BBB.
Just bought bubble tea for $5.66. The lady didn’t fill the cup up. Only part full. Do not recommend!
Bowls are good, a little light on the protein. Had a tarp boba did not taste like taro, more like jasmine. Customer service not great.
Love the food here! So fresh! I will be back for more! Reasonably priced.

Got wrong change and they didn't give me the 10% for using cash as they have written. I said taro wrong and the male cashier gave such an attitude for it. I like the 86th street location better. I expected more seeing as its in a popular and somewhat high end location

Really yummy and fresh sushi burritos and poke bowls. It was my first time having a sushi burrito and I absolutely loved it. This place is really small and cute. The only problem is there’s not much seating — but what do you expect. Most of these city locations are small. Therefore you might wanna find a place nearby to take the food to or if you really want a place to sit down you should consider some place else.
Kind & friendly staff. Haven't tried any of the food yet but their buble tea is off the hook.

Got The Triforce with salmon, tuna, and yellowtail fish. I never thought that poke bowl could be sooo bland 😔😔 I don't know what went wrong in terms of their produces, but this was quite disappointing and I never had a bad poke before. Fish didn't seem fresh, mango cuts were hard and not meaty, and white rice wasn't sushi rice I think.
Food is not fresh
Had a build-your-own and salmon oasis, both tasted very bland. Got horrible food poisoning afterwards. (This was my first and last meal of the day) Won't be going back.
Food was amazing

Great atmosphere, helpful staff, good food. I tried the salmon Oasis and it was just the right amount of spicy, and a good sized portion. Looking forward to coming back to try some of the bubble tea and drinks they have on the menu!
Best pokebowl in NYC!

Really good quality of food. Me & the Gf made our own bowls. I had yellowtail, salmon and baby octopus, all good. Plenty of toppings and fixin's to choose from. Friendly service and a clean store. High tops are nice but the chairs are metal and no backs, certainly not made for hanging around after you eat... Lol Good bubble tea too-
so good
What a terrible place. If you want a cold bowl with tasteless chicken in a puddle of sauce that makes your stomach twist in pain, stop by.
Some of the best poke I’ve ever had! The zoodle option is delicious. Huge selection of vegetables for a good price. Great sauces too
Unexpected delight For when you want to try something new
Good poke. Great selection of proteins.
Great bubble tea! Lovely flavors and consistency. Would definitely visit again! 😊

Nice place, everything looks new, and everything is clean. Employees are helpful and there is a wide selection of stuff to put in your poke bowl. I also visited some of the poke places nearby, and Poke Bowl Station majorly outranks them.
Food was okay but the employees were kind of rude and the bowl was definitely over priced. They barely filled the bowl half way which didn't help.
Splendid service! All the foods were so fresh it's crazy.

Ordered a poke bowl through seamless and was disappointed. Normally noodles or rice supposed to be hot and the fish cold. What I received was pretty much a zucchini salad with fish. The whole thing was cold. Portions also  small for price.
Spot is nice love rhe food poke all day
Best sushi bowls in Flatbush Ave,You get a lot of fish’s and the flavors are just exceptional. A true Hawaiian experience.👍👍👍👍👍 FIVES THUMBS
tasty food, clean and bright restaurant and clean restrooms :) would go again to this little gem in brooklyn
Very good Poke place. Fresh, healthy and delicious. Good prices and good sortiment of drinks
Fresh, clean tasting with interesting ingredients and sauces and very reasonably priced. Generous portions. Clean space and great location.

Great poke place. They have so many options with vegetarian and fish options. They also do a sushi burrito bowl which is awesome. They offer brown rice for the same price as white rice. The staff is friendly and accommodating. It’s a big place so plenty of room to sit and eat ear. The poke bar has so many options of toppings and sauces that there is something for everyone.

Order was for a bowl and sushirito for takeout. ended up with two bowls, and the bowl that was supposed to have been a burrito had about 3 wrong toppings. would not go back. My bowl, which was the one as ordered, was tossed before I finished it.

Fresh clean healthy food.  Everything looked delicious and with all the add ons the variety is virtually limitless.  Plan to go back again.  Service was very fast and friendly.  Great place for a low carb no carb meal.  Good value for the quality of the ingredients.

I’ve been three times now and only once was I actually served. Granted the first time I was fifteen minutes before closing so I understood closing early. Second time I had really great, albeit overpriced, poke. Third time back and once again closed early, this time thirty minutes. I get wanting to close early - but change your hours to reflect that. I’ve left work early twice now looking forward to food that hasn’t been available. I guess an hour before closing is the safe time to assume for closing here...
Seemingly small serving is actually very filling. Fresh fish and good svce.

The Rain of Fire Poke Bowl. Made with a salad base instead of rice and spicy tuna & salmon. I got a bubble milk tea to along with it. It hit the spot and was spicy enough to feed my cravings. I would surely go there again.
Very neat and tidy. The cashiers are helpful with suggestions based on your likes and dislikes
Delicious and fresh. Highly recommend getting their eel
Clean place. Fresh fish and sides.
(Translated by Google) A salad shop I frequent. The service attitude is good and the taste is good  (Original) 常去的一家沙拉店。服务态度很好 味道也不错
Love this place
So cool, everything fresh , perfect taste my favorite place!
Fresh fish with great topping choices, we've been back multiple times. One note for owner please use fresh jalapeno slices instead of pickled.
It's really nice! All the times I went it wasnt reslly busy at all so its definitely a comfortable space to be in and very enjoyable!
The best sushi in the world. You need to go there if you're in New York
Nice and clean interior.  Decent air conditioning.  Also has bubble tea. Poke is good and service is quick. Extra sauces available at the back.

Plenty of table space with backyard seating. The food tasted good and fresh and was reasonably priced. And the service was really quick.  My whole group really loved what we all ordered. The music was kind of sporadic but wasn’t terribly loud so it went some what unnoticeable.  Note - the lettuce was my least favorite part. I don’t eat rice so next time I’ll get it naked.
Clean and adorable spot. Great food. Nice place to chill, eat poke, drink bubble tea and be surrounded by little plants and books and there's an outdoor patio in the back.
Lovely poke bowls. They have set that’s you can choose from if you are not up to customizing. Also great bubble tea selections. A great addition is the patio in the back for outdoor dining!
Great poké

I really love this place! I always stop by before or after I get my hair done around the corner. They’re food is fresh and really delicious and reasonably priced!! While you have the option to kind of overload your bowl with toppings I always try to keep it on the more simple side!
Creative poke bowls are served quick and fresh. They offer signature bowls and taco combos that vary in terms of the base, the proteins and the toppings.
Great sushi and tea
Little over priced but food looks GOOD and very yummy.
The best Poké in Brooklyn.
Best place to eat and extremely fair price . Taste so good and fresh!!! Way cheaper than any other sushi place.
Great food something different
Super cheap  and delicious poke!!! veggie chicken the best.
Colorful tacos
Delish! Really friendly, young staff.
Fresh food, great options and fast service.
Poke bowls and poke tacos which look good as well. Pretty quick service when it's not busy. I'd come here again.

This place is the best place in Brooklyn for poke ! They are new fun and vibrant in design. The fish is always fresh and always has a multitude of ingredients. They also have so many different types of options here. I travel all the way from ozone park. the workers are always amazingly pleasant and the prices are great for the area they are in and quality of the food.
Really fancy pokebowl!Yam!
Finally one in BK

We were so excited to see a Poké place open in our neighborhood, and PokeBowl Station did not disappoint. The servings of fish are great, the fish is fresh, and the add-ins are crisp and amazing tasty! Haven’t tried the boba tea yet, but hoping this can be a one stop shop for two of our favorite treats!

This place is cool

love this new place！fish is so fresh，also they have my favor SPICY GINGER sauce，it' s GLUTEN FREE！
